  "text": "Five of the frozen heart tissue samples of each group were randomly picked. The heart sections were weighed and 300 mg of each sample were cut into small pieces and suspended in 1 mL of saline solution. After homogenization on ice, samples were centrifuged and the supernatants were stored at −80 ∘ C for analysis. Col-I and col-III and TGF-1 were measured by ELISA in serum and heart tissue samples according to the manufacturer's instructions [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The total protein content of each tissue sample was measured with the BCA (bicinchoninic acid) Protein Assay Kit.",
